00:07:44.292 --> 00:07:47.492
Which one is more important to you, model or harness?

00:07:48.372 --> 00:07:51.492
Like, which one between, you know what I mean,

00:07:51.532 --> 00:07:53.712
like Claude Code or the model itself,

00:07:53.732 --> 00:07:55.852
which one is more important?

00:07:56.612 --> 00:07:59.332
Right. I think they're both very important.

00:07:59.692 --> 00:08:00.582
I think what we've found is that

00:08:00.612 --> 00:08:07.302
the model and harness work together to achieve the goal.

00:08:08.172 --> 00:08:13.272
I think in a lot of ways, yeah,

00:08:13.332 --> 00:08:17.472
I think there is a distinction,

00:08:17.512 --> 00:08:20.219
but I think in a lot of ways they're kind of the same.

00:08:21.272 --> 00:08:23.132
In the sense that it's almost like if you think about it,

00:08:24.792 --> 00:08:25.802
if you look at the model itself,

00:08:25.832 --> 00:08:28.559
the model is considered as one giant thing,

00:08:28.632 --> 00:08:30.552
but if you look at the inside of the model,

00:08:30.592 --> 00:08:33.852
there are like different stages and different components.

00:08:34.472 --> 00:08:37.001
And so we group them together and call it a model,

00:08:37.032 --> 00:08:39.592
and then we group something like Claude Code together

00:08:39.631 --> 00:08:41.662
and call it a harness,

00:08:41.792 --> 00:08:43.871
but they're ultimately just different stages

00:08:43.912 --> 00:08:48.092
in the pipeline of the product that we deliver.

00:08:48.572 --> 00:08:49.212
In my opinion,

00:08:49.272 --> 00:08:52.012
both the model and harness are very important,

00:08:52.052 --> 00:08:54.032
and I think the model and harness work together

00:08:54.072 --> 00:08:57.372
to actually give you the agentic coding results

00:08:57.392 --> 00:08:59.052
that you see with Claude Code.

00:08:59.692 --> 00:09:00.702
In a lot of ways,

00:09:01.712 --> 00:09:04.192
I think both are extremely important,

00:09:04.312 --> 00:09:07.762
and so it's hard to say.

00:09:08.052 --> 00:09:10.172
Although the model, as you can think,

00:09:10.232 --> 00:09:11.492
it's actually a little bit more,

00:09:14.432 --> 00:09:17.352
like you can use it for more than just with the harness.

00:09:17.392 --> 00:09:19.232
Like you can actually use it on claude.ai,

00:09:19.292 --> 00:09:21.243
you can use it like as an API,

00:09:21.332 --> 00:09:24.045
and so it's a little bit more general purpose

00:09:24.552 --> 00:09:27.292
than the specific harness with Claude Code.

